== English ==
=== Verb form ===
# (''Commonwealth English, slang'') present participle of [[seagull]]; the practice, in [[w:Rugby Union|Rugby Union]], of forwards running in the back lines (see [[w:rugby union positions|rugby union positions]])
#:'''usage note''':Other inflections are rare with this meaning.
#:'''quotations''':
#:*2002:"[...] when you need cover for the fullback because of the bombs raining down, when the walking maul requires every forward to quit '''seagulling''' and actually do some hard graft, then the rest of the game opens up." &mdash; [http://groups.google.com/group/rec.sport.rugby.union/msg/74b3c28f7c47d06c]
#:*2002:"On hand was '''seagulling''' number eight Dave Hodges to cross for the all-important try." &mdash; [http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport2/hi/rugby_union/european/2561513.stm BBC Sport]
#:*2005:"Scotland run it wide right, to Hogg '''seagulling''' on the wing, but he is pushed into touch just short." &mdash; [http://www.sportinglife.com/rugbyunion/sixnations2005/news/story_get.cgi?STORY_NAME=rugby/05/02/26/manual_132928.html ''Sporting Life'']

#("British Seagull outboard enthusiasts, slang") present participle of [[seagull]]; the practice of using a British Seagull outboard.
